  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Recovery Assistance to Flood Affected Communities of Swat</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Affected population(s)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Formation of Village Committees. Provision of cash grants for micro-enterprises. Cash for work opportunities to landless flood affected people.  Provision of agriculture inputs to the flood affected farmers. Training of farmers on integrated crop management.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project funded by UNDP was initiatied in Swat to improve food security of flood affected communities through restoration of their livelihoods. A total of 10 village committes (5 of women and 5 of men) were formed to spearehead the livelihood recovery process in their target villages.  After formation of the village committees the benificiaries for each component were identified in consultation with the target communities as per beneficiary selection criteria. A total of 52 cash for work schemes were identified and completed in the target villages that helped to provide cash for work opportunities to 600 landless flood affected labourers within their target villages. Under the second component, 600 farmers were provided with vouchers to get agriculture inputs through the market days to reinvigorate their farm based livelihoods. 20 integrated crop management trainings were provided to the target farmers to capacitate them to effectively utilize the given agriculture inputs. Under component three, 35 landless flood affected people were provided with the cash grants to set up their own micro-enterprises in their respective villages.</narrative>
  </description>
